1
00:01:39,010 --> 00:01:41,394
[Episode 11]

2
00:01:43,560 --> 00:01:44,870
Done.

3
00:01:44,870 --> 00:01:46,920
150 yuan.

4
00:01:46,920 --> 00:01:49,430
You're pretty good at this.

5
00:01:49,430 --> 00:01:51,542
Go ahead.

6
00:01:57,562 --> 00:01:58,590
What are you doing?

7
00:01:58,590 --> 00:02:00,870
I'm asking you to do me a favor.

8
00:02:00,870 --> 00:02:03,006
Help me talk her into going abroad.

9
00:02:05,430 --> 00:02:06,870
If you don't know what to do with your money,

10
00:02:06,870 --> 00:02:09,260
go sponsor some underprivileged kids.

11
00:02:13,840 --> 00:02:15,904
Got quite a temper.

12
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:35,630
<i>People never do something for others
without expecting anything in return.</i>

13
00:02:35,630 --> 00:02:38,844
<i>If they go out of their way,
there must be a reason.</i>

14
00:02:52,880 --> 00:02:54,760
Hey, Fuzz.

15
00:02:54,760 --> 00:02:55,861
Are you in bed yet?

16
00:02:55,861 --> 00:02:57,860
Let's hang out around.

17
00:02:57,860 --> 00:03:00,630
<i>No, thanks.
I've got work tomorrow. I have to sleep now.</i>

18
00:03:00,630 --> 00:03:03,139
<i>Wu, you get to bed early, too.</i>

19
00:03:07,933 --> 00:03:09,320
Hey, Hu.

20
00:03:09,320 --> 00:03:10,630
Are you asleep?

21
00:03:10,630 --> 00:03:12,360
Do you want to hang out with me?

22
00:03:12,360 --> 00:03:15,030
<i>I'm going to work with Fuzz tomorrow.</i>

23
00:03:15,030 --> 00:03:17,140
<i>We'll meet at four, Wu.</i>

24
00:03:17,140 --> 00:03:19,160
<i>- Don't forget it.</i>
- Okay.

25
00:03:55,520 --> 00:03:57,420
Come on,

26
00:03:59,200 --> 00:04:02,360
it's only four-something in the morning.
What are you doing here?

27
00:04:02,360 --> 00:04:03,680
It's already light out.

28
00:04:03,680 --> 00:04:06,590
Why were you in Wu's room
in the middle of the night?

29
00:04:06,590 --> 00:04:09,280
I was sleeping, of course.

30
00:04:10,520 --> 00:04:12,963
Something came up last night.

31
00:04:12,963 --> 00:04:15,470
I had nowhere to go,
so I stayed here overnight.

32
00:04:15,470 --> 00:04:17,510
You are all here.

33
00:04:17,510 --> 00:04:20,230
Are you addicted to picking up strays?

34
00:04:20,230 --> 00:04:22,270
First, Qing Ye, well, she's your cousin,
but this guy? Why?

35
00:04:22,270 --> 00:04:24,760
Doesn't your dad need help
loading and unloading cargo?

36
00:04:24,760 --> 00:04:27,120
- You're going or not?
- I never said I'd go.

37
00:04:27,120 --> 00:04:30,008
But you can't just stay here for free.

38
00:04:30,008 --> 00:04:31,320
I already paid you.

39
00:04:31,320 --> 00:04:32,590
Here,

40
00:04:32,590 --> 00:04:35,500
that doesn't mean everything is settled.

41
00:04:46,320 --> 00:04:49,030
What's that smell? It's awful.

42
00:04:49,030 --> 00:04:50,880
It's the smell of seafood.

43
00:04:50,880 --> 00:04:53,520
Is this where you usually work?

44
00:04:53,520 --> 00:04:54,698
Yeah, what do you think?

45
00:04:54,698 --> 00:04:56,341
Just the four of us?

46
00:04:56,341 --> 00:04:58,910
No, there are plenty of people here.

47
00:04:58,910 --> 00:05:01,880
You're pretty delicate. Don't push yourself.

48
00:05:01,880 --> 00:05:04,230
Don't judge me by appearance.

49
00:05:04,230 --> 00:05:06,442
Where do I change into work clothes?

50
00:05:07,390 --> 00:05:09,319
Over there.

51
00:05:12,710 --> 00:05:14,230
Okay.

52
00:05:14,230 --> 00:05:16,030
Sir, be careful.

53
00:05:16,030 --> 00:05:17,999
Don't worry.

54
00:05:25,830 --> 00:05:27,000
New guy!

55
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:28,880
Go throw up over there if you have to.

56
00:05:28,880 --> 00:05:31,924
It's all seafood around here.
Don't get it dirty.

57
00:05:36,720 --> 00:05:40,220
- Don't push yourself too hard.
- I'm fine.

58
00:05:42,600 --> 00:05:44,030
Good for you.

59
00:05:44,030 --> 00:05:45,390
Hu.

60
00:05:45,390 --> 00:05:47,946
- Hold this for me.
- Okay.

61
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:56,446
Why not go home?

62
00:05:58,270 --> 00:05:59,390
I'm fine.

63
00:05:59,390 --> 00:06:01,680
I've only seen seafood in restaurants.

64
00:06:01,680 --> 00:06:05,080
It's my first time being this close.
I can't handle that smell.

65
00:06:05,080 --> 00:06:06,790
If so,

66
00:06:06,790 --> 00:06:08,590
how about loading the car over there?

67
00:06:08,590 --> 00:06:10,080
The smell over there is faint.

68
00:06:10,080 --> 00:06:11,841
Sure.

69
00:06:17,440 --> 00:06:19,460
Xing Wu.

70
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:22,710
Ye.

71
00:06:22,710 --> 00:06:25,270
- Where are you going?
- I'm going for a jog.

72
00:06:25,270 --> 00:06:28,107
Sit here. We need to talk.

73
00:06:30,230 --> 00:06:31,720
Auntie,

74
00:06:31,720 --> 00:06:33,640
this mask really fits your face.

75
00:06:33,640 --> 00:06:39,320
Of course, after all, it's your present to me.
It's brand is Clinic.

76
00:06:39,320 --> 00:06:40,590
Clinique.

77
00:06:40,590 --> 00:06:42,270
Right. Whatever it is.

78
00:06:42,270 --> 00:06:43,680
Yesterday,

79
00:06:43,680 --> 00:06:47,520
you told me that Meng is taking you abroad.

80
00:06:47,520 --> 00:06:49,390
I was so worried about you.

81
00:06:49,390 --> 00:06:51,000
I haven't had a good night's sleep.

82
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:52,470
As your auntie,

83
00:06:52,470 --> 00:06:54,931
I have to talk to you

84
00:06:56,080 --> 00:06:57,640
about going abroad with him.

85
00:06:57,640 --> 00:07:00,000
You really need to think about it.

86
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:02,470
It's like playing Mahjong,

87
00:07:02,470 --> 00:07:04,880
you look at your tiles
and think you've got a big win coming,

88
00:07:04,880 --> 00:07:07,710
but then you end up
feeding someone else a monster hand.

89
00:07:07,710 --> 00:07:09,640
No wonder Mahjong is a classic.

90
00:07:09,640 --> 00:07:12,230
I know what you mean.

91
00:07:12,230 --> 00:07:13,830
That actually makes a lot of sense.

92
00:07:13,830 --> 00:07:15,760
Look, I've been there.

93
00:07:15,760 --> 00:07:18,520
I've made mistakes,
so I don't want you to do the same.

94
00:07:18,520 --> 00:07:21,000
You need to keep your eyes open
when it comes to people.

95
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:22,910
Especially when it comes to men.

96
00:07:22,910 --> 00:07:24,560
You can't be rash

97
00:07:24,560 --> 00:07:26,360
and elope with him.

98
00:07:26,360 --> 00:07:29,470
Auntie, where did you even get that?
That's not elopement.

99
00:07:29,470 --> 00:07:31,390
We're going abroad for advanced study.

100
00:07:31,390 --> 00:07:34,320
Studying abroad? What's the difference
between that and elopement?

101
00:07:34,320 --> 00:07:35,680
That's even more unreliable.

102
00:07:35,680 --> 00:07:39,200
I've read those job interviews
and certificates of property.

103
00:07:39,200 --> 00:07:42,560
- Those are real documents.
- What do his parents think?

104
00:07:42,560 --> 00:07:43,910
Back then,

105
00:07:43,910 --> 00:07:46,560
Xing Wu made his own decision
to bring me back from Beijing

106
00:07:46,560 --> 00:07:47,760
without asking for your permission.

107
00:07:47,760 --> 00:07:49,680
Meng is nowhere near Xing Wu.

108
00:07:49,680 --> 00:07:51,200
I know my son.

109
00:07:51,200 --> 00:07:54,390
I raised him, so I can vouch for his character.

110
00:07:54,390 --> 00:07:55,560
Anyway, bottom line is,

111
00:07:55,560 --> 00:07:57,560
if he hasn't earned my approval,

112
00:07:57,560 --> 00:08:00,985
I'm not letting you go abroad with him.

113
00:08:02,350 --> 00:08:03,680
Okay.

114
00:08:03,680 --> 00:08:05,030
I'm with you.

115
00:08:05,030 --> 00:08:07,320
- I'll go jogging then.
- Okay.

116
00:08:09,390 --> 00:08:11,457
- I'll wait right here.
- Okay.

117
00:08:12,390 --> 00:08:14,590
- Your buns.
- Thank you.

118
00:08:20,503 --> 00:08:21,910
Thank you.

119
00:08:21,910 --> 00:08:23,790
You've emptied your stomach, right?

120
00:08:23,790 --> 00:08:25,460
Eat up.

121
00:08:31,640 --> 00:08:33,710
This place really rubs off on me.

122
00:08:33,710 --> 00:08:36,470
Qing Ye has become quite different from before.

123
00:08:36,470 --> 00:08:38,040
How is she different?

124
00:08:38,040 --> 00:08:39,360
She would have chosen to

125
00:08:39,360 --> 00:08:42,750
go abroad without hesitation

126
00:08:42,750 --> 00:08:44,750
instead of wasting her time here

127
00:08:44,750 --> 00:08:46,674
to run a barbershop.

128
00:08:47,750 --> 00:08:49,710
I also asked her if she feels like
staying here is a waste of time.

129
00:08:49,710 --> 00:08:51,997
She said no.

130
00:08:54,750 --> 00:08:56,750
It's true that
the environment can change people.

131
00:08:56,750 --> 00:08:58,120
But Qing Ye

132
00:08:58,120 --> 00:09:01,080
has the power to change the environment too.

133
00:09:01,080 --> 00:09:02,470
<i>- Good morning, Ye.
- Good morning, Auntie.</i>

134
00:09:02,470 --> 00:09:04,583
<i>- Did you have breakfast?
- No, I'll eat after my jog.</i>

135
00:09:04,583 --> 00:09:05,720
<i>- Save me some.
- Sure.</i>

136
00:09:05,720 --> 00:09:07,590
<i>- Morning, Qing Ye, working out?
- Morning, Uncle Pocky.</i>

137
00:09:07,590 --> 00:09:08,870
When she wants to do something...

138
00:09:08,870 --> 00:09:11,160
<i>- Good luck with your business.</i>
- she puts her whole heart into it.

139
00:09:11,160 --> 00:09:13,280
<i>You have a way with words.</i>

140
00:09:13,990 --> 00:09:16,230
<i>Bo, why not jogging?</i>

141
00:09:16,230 --> 00:09:17,680
<i>- Lose some weight and eat healthily.
- Got it.</i>

142
00:09:17,680 --> 00:09:19,680
People are naturally drawn to her
without even realizing it,

143
00:09:19,680 --> 00:09:24,080
- and they end up standing with her...
<i>- Grandma Zhao, this eggplant looks good.</i>

144
00:09:24,080 --> 00:09:25,691
<i>You can pick it when it grows up.</i>

145
00:09:25,691 --> 00:09:27,400
<i>Great. I'm off.</i>

146
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:29,480
And in her light,

147
00:09:29,480 --> 00:09:31,960
we'll see who we really are.

148
00:09:34,080 --> 00:09:35,920
I admit that

149
00:09:35,920 --> 00:09:38,870
she had fun here,

150
00:09:38,870 --> 00:09:41,630
but that was what she did on her days off.

151
00:09:41,630 --> 00:09:44,710
She deserves a bigger world.

152
00:09:44,710 --> 00:09:46,350
If you really have her best interests at heart,

153
00:09:46,350 --> 00:09:49,200
talk her into going abroad with me.

154
00:09:51,040 --> 00:09:53,160
I'm not her,

155
00:09:53,160 --> 00:09:54,590
so I can't interfere with her choice

156
00:09:54,590 --> 00:09:56,827
with my own expectation.

157
00:09:59,350 --> 00:10:01,590
What if I say

158
00:10:01,590 --> 00:10:04,845
I'm providing her with the life she wants?

159
00:10:12,772 --> 00:10:13,920
Watch this.

160
00:10:13,920 --> 00:10:17,280
<i>♪ Happy birthday to you ♪</i>

161
00:10:17,280 --> 00:10:20,990
<i>♪ happy birthday to you ♪</i>

162
00:10:20,990 --> 00:10:23,484
<i>Make a wish.</i>

163
00:10:23,484 --> 00:10:25,040
<i>When I'm 20,</i>

164
00:10:25,040 --> 00:10:26,280
<i>I'll be studying</i>

165
00:10:26,280 --> 00:10:29,560
<i>for a business degree at
a top-ten university in the world.</i>

166
00:10:29,560 --> 00:10:31,870
<i>And I'm going to travel around the world.</i>

167
00:10:31,870 --> 00:10:34,280
<i>I'm going to Egypt to see the pyramids.</i>

168
00:10:34,280 --> 00:10:36,040
<i>I'm going to Pompeii.</i>

169
00:10:36,040 --> 00:10:40,320
<i>And I'm going to Chile
to see a volcanic eruption.</i>

170
00:10:40,320 --> 00:10:42,750
<i>As long as I'm willing,</i>

171
00:10:42,750 --> 00:10:45,825
<i>the world is at my feet.</i>

172
00:10:46,750 --> 00:10:49,440
This is the real her.

173
00:10:50,630 --> 00:10:53,320
Zhazhating is her temporary shelter.

174
00:10:53,320 --> 00:10:55,080
Now the wind's picked up,

175
00:10:55,080 --> 00:10:57,846
and you have to help her set sail again.

176
00:11:02,630 --> 00:11:05,490
Why do you think I can talk her into it?

177
00:11:06,800 --> 00:11:08,510
Whether you can convince her is one thing.

178
00:11:08,510 --> 00:11:11,300
But trying is better than not trying at all.

179
00:11:14,530 --> 00:11:16,300
Xing Wu.

180
00:11:17,350 --> 00:11:19,202
Xing Wu.

181
00:11:29,920 --> 00:11:31,510
<i>As long as I'm willing,</i>

182
00:11:31,510 --> 00:11:34,544
<i>the world is at my feet.</i>

183
00:11:55,960 --> 00:11:58,739
Why are you two together?

184
00:12:00,240 --> 00:12:02,280
It's a long story.

185
00:12:03,830 --> 00:12:06,160
Take the fish back to appease my mom.

186
00:12:06,160 --> 00:12:08,320
You can't stay at my house for free.

187
00:12:08,320 --> 00:12:11,960
Okay. Think about what I said.

188
00:12:11,960 --> 00:12:13,440
What did you say?

189
00:12:13,440 --> 00:12:15,400
It's a secret between men.

190
00:12:15,400 --> 00:12:17,168
I'm leaving.

191
00:12:19,230 --> 00:12:21,141
Did you have breakfast?

192
00:12:25,240 --> 00:12:27,560
What hairstyle do you want?

193
00:12:27,560 --> 00:12:29,683
Perm my hair like this.

194
00:12:30,510 --> 00:12:32,560
Is this the most popular hairstyle around here?

195
00:12:32,560 --> 00:12:33,920
Yes.

196
00:12:33,920 --> 00:12:38,800
- Then do my hair like this.
- Sure. This is Liu Nian's signature hairstyle.

197
00:12:38,800 --> 00:12:40,510
I'll make sure he gives you a really good perm.

198
00:12:40,510 --> 00:12:41,870
You'll be satisfied.

199
00:12:41,870 --> 00:12:43,470
Fang, give me a discount.

200
00:12:43,470 --> 00:12:44,960
20 percent off.

201
00:12:44,960 --> 00:12:47,055
You're so generous.

202
00:12:47,750 --> 00:12:50,470
- Take good care of her.
- No problem.

203
00:12:52,110 --> 00:12:53,865
Auntie.

204
00:12:56,750 --> 00:12:58,555
Call me Ms. Li.

205
00:12:59,590 --> 00:13:03,560
Ms. Li, I was working at the dock this morning
and brought you a fish.

206
00:13:03,560 --> 00:13:05,903
You went to work.

207
00:13:06,590 --> 00:13:10,105
Good. Smells like a Zhazhating resident.

208
00:13:11,600 --> 00:13:13,080
I was just looking for you,

209
00:13:13,080 --> 00:13:15,400
and you came right to me.

210
00:13:15,400 --> 00:13:17,624
Give me the fish.

211
00:13:20,720 --> 00:13:23,160
You're an adult, right?

212
00:13:27,080 --> 00:13:30,680
Yes, so...

213
00:13:30,680 --> 00:13:31,830
The sweet cake

214
00:13:31,830 --> 00:13:35,520
you brought yesterday distracted me

215
00:13:35,520 --> 00:13:38,870
that I didn't realize you were trying to
take Qing Ye away.

216
00:13:38,870 --> 00:13:41,621
No, Ms. Li, you're mistaken.
Qing Ye and I are just friends.

217
00:13:41,621 --> 00:13:43,760
I just want to help her.

218
00:13:43,760 --> 00:13:46,470
You city kids are smooth talkers,

219
00:13:46,470 --> 00:13:47,800
good with words.

220
00:13:47,800 --> 00:13:50,240
I can't outtalk you.

221
00:13:50,240 --> 00:13:53,110
But today, I'm having you here

222
00:13:53,110 --> 00:13:54,809
to test your ability.

223
00:13:54,809 --> 00:13:56,890
Let's see how much you can handle.

224
00:13:56,890 --> 00:13:57,960
Fine.

225
00:13:57,960 --> 00:14:00,942
Ms. Li, what should I do?

226
00:14:01,870 --> 00:14:04,590
As the saying goes,

227
00:14:04,590 --> 00:14:07,400
a man's courage is as big as

228
00:14:07,400 --> 00:14:10,088
his capacity for liquor.

229
00:14:13,350 --> 00:14:15,040
No problem, Ms. Li.

230
00:14:15,040 --> 00:14:17,920
I've been bold since I was a kid.

231
00:14:17,920 --> 00:14:19,680
Let's start.

232
00:14:24,750 --> 00:14:28,041
Well done, young man.

233
00:14:36,160 --> 00:14:38,073
You're good.

234
00:14:38,073 --> 00:14:39,110
Here.

235
00:14:39,110 --> 00:14:41,482
Let's go on.

236
00:14:44,440 --> 00:14:46,600
Meng.

237
00:14:46,600 --> 00:14:48,480
Meng.

238
00:14:49,630 --> 00:14:51,759
Wake up.

239
00:14:57,750 --> 00:15:00,230
Bold, uh?

240
00:15:19,990 --> 00:15:22,320
Meng Rui Hang wants me to talk to you

241
00:15:22,320 --> 00:15:24,537
into going abroad with him.

242
00:15:27,200 --> 00:15:30,230
He's got the wrong person.

243
00:15:30,230 --> 00:15:31,800
You said

244
00:15:31,800 --> 00:15:33,846
you wouldn't interfere with my life choices.

245
00:15:36,440 --> 00:15:38,072
Perhaps.

246
00:15:38,750 --> 00:15:41,006
You want me to go with him?

247
00:15:48,080 --> 00:15:50,040
I think

248
00:15:50,040 --> 00:15:52,598
it's good for you.

249
00:15:58,173 --> 00:15:59,859
Why?

250
00:16:05,230 --> 00:16:07,110
Do you know the difference

251
00:16:07,110 --> 00:16:10,124
between migratory and resident birds?

252
00:16:11,400 --> 00:16:13,712
What are you trying to say?

253
00:16:15,949 --> 00:16:19,230
Resident birds don't migrate with the seasons.

254
00:16:19,230 --> 00:16:21,814
They grow where they were born.

255
00:16:22,470 --> 00:16:24,800
But migratory birds are different.

256
00:16:24,800 --> 00:16:26,920
When winter comes,

257
00:16:26,920 --> 00:16:29,230
Siberian swans fly here

258
00:16:29,230 --> 00:16:31,320
for a short winter.

259
00:16:31,320 --> 00:16:34,440
When the weather warms up
and flowers bloom in spring,

260
00:16:34,440 --> 00:16:37,414
they'll fly back to where they came from.

261
00:16:38,470 --> 00:16:40,844
You think I'm a migratory bird?

262
00:16:44,320 --> 00:16:46,920
You should go back to your life.

263
00:16:46,920 --> 00:16:49,419
Zhazhating doesn't suit you,

264
00:16:50,440 --> 00:16:52,816
and it's not worth staying for.

265
00:16:56,200 --> 00:16:57,560
Whether it's worth it or not,

266
00:16:57,560 --> 00:16:59,505
I'll make decisions myself.

267
00:17:00,230 --> 00:17:02,320
Don't forget your promise.

268
00:17:02,320 --> 00:17:04,104
If I leave,

269
00:17:04,840 --> 00:17:06,985
remember to see me off.

270
00:17:14,960 --> 00:17:16,795
It's a deal.

271
00:17:18,400 --> 00:17:20,037
Okay.

272
00:17:37,680 --> 00:17:40,015
He's so heavy.

273
00:17:41,070 --> 00:17:43,714
Fang, leave him here for a while.
I'm exhausted.

274
00:17:43,714 --> 00:17:45,638
All right, come on.

275
00:17:46,310 --> 00:17:48,148
Easy.

276
00:17:50,710 --> 00:17:53,880
He looks fit, but how come

277
00:17:53,880 --> 00:17:56,455
he can't hold his liquor?

278
00:17:56,455 --> 00:17:58,841
He needs more practice.

279
00:18:00,400 --> 00:18:02,030
What's wrong with him?

280
00:18:02,030 --> 00:18:03,470
He's drunk.

281
00:18:03,470 --> 00:18:05,240
Drunk?

282
00:18:05,240 --> 00:18:08,037
In the morning? Who did he drink with?

283
00:18:08,830 --> 00:18:10,120
Just one bottle and he fell asleep.

284
00:18:10,120 --> 00:18:14,510
I just wanted to see how much he can drink.

285
00:18:14,510 --> 00:18:16,880
I didn't expect him to be so reckless.

286
00:18:16,880 --> 00:18:19,400
I thought he could hold his liquor,
but he failed.

287
00:18:19,400 --> 00:18:21,470
But I can tell

288
00:18:21,470 --> 00:18:24,543
that he cares about you.

289
00:18:25,230 --> 00:18:26,990
But he's reckless,

290
00:18:26,990 --> 00:18:28,840
and that makes him less reliable than Wu,
Right?

291
00:18:28,840 --> 00:18:30,959
Think of Wu,

292
00:18:30,959 --> 00:18:34,230
he's down-to-earth, reliable and capable.

293
00:18:34,230 --> 00:18:35,840
Well, anyway,

294
00:18:35,840 --> 00:18:37,640
in terms of going abroad,

295
00:18:37,640 --> 00:18:40,600
I think you should think it over.

296
00:18:40,600 --> 00:18:41,920
Don't worry, Auntie.

297
00:18:41,920 --> 00:18:43,804
I know what I'm doing.

298
00:18:44,480 --> 00:18:46,510
Qing Ye.

299
00:18:46,510 --> 00:18:48,510
Come with me.

300
00:18:48,510 --> 00:18:50,640
Go abroad with me.

301
00:18:50,640 --> 00:18:52,901
He's so devoted.

302
00:18:54,070 --> 00:18:56,551
- I can keep going.
- Oh, come on. Go ahead.

303
00:18:56,551 --> 00:18:58,076
Fang, I'm wiped out.

304
00:18:58,076 --> 00:19:01,320
Hurry up. Take him into the room,
otherwise, customers will see him.

305
00:19:01,320 --> 00:19:02,560
Wait.

306
00:19:02,560 --> 00:19:04,360
Lie him on Wu's bed.

307
00:19:04,360 --> 00:19:06,920
- Give me a hand.
- Here.

308
00:19:06,920 --> 00:19:08,877
Easy.

309
00:19:21,600 --> 00:19:22,710
I'm not drunk yet.

310
00:19:22,710 --> 00:19:25,205
Come on, stop it.

311
00:19:25,990 --> 00:19:28,180
I'll get him some water.

312
00:19:50,270 --> 00:19:52,160
<i>Can I come in?</i>

313
00:19:52,160 --> 00:19:54,916
<i>Hold on. I'll be right here.</i>

314
00:19:58,386 --> 00:20:01,068
<i>What's up? Anything I can do?</i>

315
00:20:40,016 --> 00:20:42,510
Hello? Who is this?

316
00:20:43,680 --> 00:20:46,028
<i>Did Meng Rui Hang come to see you?</i>

317
00:20:47,120 --> 00:20:49,647
I don't have to answer you.

318
00:20:50,880 --> 00:20:54,681
<i>Do you know he turned against
his parents because of you?</i>

319
00:22:07,270 --> 00:22:11,160
Taking time off during work hours

320
00:22:11,160 --> 00:22:13,640
doesn't suit you, workaholic.

321
00:22:13,640 --> 00:22:14,960
What's up?

322
00:22:14,960 --> 00:22:17,960
I've been sitting for too long.
So I get up and stretch.

323
00:22:17,960 --> 00:22:20,270
You've worked hard.

324
00:22:20,270 --> 00:22:22,344
I brought you some food.

325
00:22:23,070 --> 00:22:25,470
Thanks.

326
00:22:25,470 --> 00:22:27,605
There's a strong wind warning tonight.

327
00:22:27,605 --> 00:22:31,330
It's too Dangerous to ride on the road.
Stay here overnight.

328
00:22:32,560 --> 00:22:34,402
All right.

329
00:22:36,310 --> 00:22:39,600
Well, I heard that

330
00:22:39,600 --> 00:22:41,440
Qing Ye's childhood friend

331
00:22:41,440 --> 00:22:43,506
is taking her abroad,

332
00:22:46,120 --> 00:22:48,007
Really?

333
00:22:54,960 --> 00:22:57,270
She was planning to go abroad.

334
00:22:57,270 --> 00:22:59,880
It's just getting back on track.

335
00:23:20,200 --> 00:23:22,120
It's good that she left before she gets

336
00:23:22,120 --> 00:23:23,888
too attached to this place.

337
00:23:46,270 --> 00:23:47,920
Qing Ye.

338
00:23:47,920 --> 00:23:49,700
Qing Ye.

339
00:24:06,960 --> 00:24:08,819
Where's Qing Ye?

340
00:24:09,710 --> 00:24:10,840
She left.

341
00:24:10,840 --> 00:24:12,920
Really?

342
00:24:12,920 --> 00:24:15,200
Why didn't she tell me?

343
00:24:15,200 --> 00:24:17,656
With Meng?

344
00:24:18,840 --> 00:24:21,884
I'm still a little worried about her
leaving with him.

345
00:24:21,884 --> 00:24:23,270
They're only teenagers in high school.

346
00:24:23,270 --> 00:24:25,845
What if something happens to them?

347
00:24:28,310 --> 00:24:30,960
<i>You should go back to your life.</i>

348
00:24:30,960 --> 00:24:33,120
<i>Zhazhating doesn't suit you,</i>

349
00:24:33,120 --> 00:24:35,340
<i>and it's not worth staying for.</i>

350
00:24:36,030 --> 00:24:37,440
<i>Whether it's worth it or not,</i>

351
00:24:37,440 --> 00:24:39,510
<i>I'll make decisions myself.</i>

352
00:24:40,510 --> 00:24:42,885
<i>Don't forget your promise.</i>

353
00:24:44,070 --> 00:24:46,400
<i>If I leave,</i>

354
00:24:46,400 --> 00:24:48,692
<i>remember to see me off.</i>

355
00:24:51,070 --> 00:24:52,640
Wu!

356
00:24:56,600 --> 00:24:58,710
Good grief.

357
00:25:14,790 --> 00:25:17,100
Do you know what this is?

358
00:25:19,840 --> 00:25:21,470
Rice?

359
00:25:22,640 --> 00:25:24,510
No, it's not rice.

360
00:25:24,510 --> 00:25:26,200
It's a weed.

361
00:25:26,200 --> 00:25:28,802
It grows together with rice.

362
00:25:29,640 --> 00:25:31,310
What's the difference?

363
00:25:31,310 --> 00:25:34,513
Qing Ye, you don't need to know
the difference between the rice and weeds

364
00:25:34,513 --> 00:25:36,750
or how fishermen fish,

365
00:25:36,750 --> 00:25:39,120
let alone loading fish by yourself.

366
00:25:39,120 --> 00:25:41,310
You don't belong here.

367
00:25:41,310 --> 00:25:44,400
We can have a better life in Beijing.

368
00:25:46,400 --> 00:25:48,378
Will it be better?

369
00:25:52,440 --> 00:25:54,230
There are things that

370
00:25:54,230 --> 00:25:55,640
once you know,

371
00:25:55,640 --> 00:25:58,470
you can never go back to not knowing.

372
00:25:58,470 --> 00:26:00,160
For example, I know

373
00:26:00,160 --> 00:26:02,840
how painful it is to lose a family member.

374
00:26:02,840 --> 00:26:04,880
That's why I can't just stand by

375
00:26:04,880 --> 00:26:07,470
and watch you break up with your family,

376
00:26:07,470 --> 00:26:09,550
while taking your kindness for granted.

377
00:26:09,550 --> 00:26:12,550
You already know?

378
00:26:12,550 --> 00:26:14,030
He Le Ling told me about it.

379
00:26:14,030 --> 00:26:16,960
She said you turned against your parents
and ran away from home.

380
00:26:16,960 --> 00:26:19,230
Qing Ye, I can solve this.

381
00:26:19,230 --> 00:26:21,400
I know.

382
00:26:21,400 --> 00:26:24,880
If I go abroad with you,

383
00:26:24,880 --> 00:26:27,840
maybe another kind of life will open up for me.

384
00:26:27,840 --> 00:26:29,230
But I don't want that.

385
00:26:29,230 --> 00:26:31,840
I still want to rely on myself
to get through all the obstacles

386
00:26:31,840 --> 00:26:34,400
and live the life I want.

387
00:26:37,710 --> 00:26:40,274
Someone told me

388
00:26:41,360 --> 00:26:44,400
that I could still

389
00:26:44,400 --> 00:26:46,200
stand on my own

390
00:26:46,200 --> 00:26:48,581
and live with pride, just like before.

391
00:26:51,440 --> 00:26:52,990
The bus is almost here.

392
00:26:52,990 --> 00:26:54,440
When you get to the county,

393
00:26:54,440 --> 00:26:57,096
take a taxi to the train station.

394
00:27:00,880 --> 00:27:02,400
I don't know

395
00:27:02,400 --> 00:27:04,298
when we'll meet again.

396
00:27:06,230 --> 00:27:08,637
Call me when you get home.

397
00:27:09,920 --> 00:27:11,470
I'm still worried about you.

398
00:27:11,470 --> 00:27:13,600
Rest assured.

399
00:27:13,600 --> 00:27:15,960
I can do well anywhere.

400
00:27:16,960 --> 00:27:18,360
The next time we meet,

401
00:27:18,360 --> 00:27:22,237
I'm sure we'll become better ourselves.

402
00:27:29,790 --> 00:27:30,880
Goodbye.

403
00:27:30,880 --> 00:27:32,714
I'm off.

404
00:27:38,200 --> 00:27:39,440
Qing Ye,

405
00:27:39,440 --> 00:27:40,710
as long as you need me,

406
00:27:40,710 --> 00:27:43,222
just give me a call and I'll be there.

407
00:28:46,060 --> 00:28:48,063
You didn't leave?

408
00:28:48,790 --> 00:28:50,820
Where to?

409
00:28:58,920 --> 00:29:01,257
Will you go home with me?

410
00:29:01,990 --> 00:29:03,894
Of course.

411
00:29:06,510 --> 00:29:08,680
But before heading home,

412
00:29:08,680 --> 00:29:10,985
I still have a place to go, come with me.

413
00:29:11,710 --> 00:29:13,718
Where to?

414
00:29:15,920 --> 00:29:17,920
[Prime Furniture]

415
00:29:21,550 --> 00:29:23,120
I've been asking you the whole way,

416
00:29:23,120 --> 00:29:25,480
and we ended up buying a mattress?

417
00:29:25,480 --> 00:29:27,600
You can't sleep on cardboard boxes forever.

418
00:29:27,600 --> 00:29:28,680
It's bad for your back,

419
00:29:28,680 --> 00:29:31,510
and I feel bad about it.

420
00:29:31,510 --> 00:29:34,270
Where did you get the money to buy it?

421
00:29:34,270 --> 00:29:35,880
I sold my clothes
on the secondhand trading app.

422
00:29:35,880 --> 00:29:37,840
Got a lot of money for it.

423
00:29:37,840 --> 00:29:39,437
Look.

424
00:29:40,470 --> 00:29:42,470
Sending packages is a hassle here,

425
00:29:42,470 --> 00:29:44,270
so I took the clothes to the county
to send them off.

426
00:29:44,270 --> 00:29:47,400
You carried it all the way from Beijing
and sold them just like that?

427
00:29:48,790 --> 00:29:50,400
Your sleep quality

428
00:29:50,400 --> 00:29:53,230
matters more to me than these clothes do.

429
00:29:53,230 --> 00:29:54,600
Besides, the new semester is about to start.

430
00:29:54,600 --> 00:29:57,640
All students wear uniforms,
leaving these clothes idle.

431
00:30:00,400 --> 00:30:02,203
Thank you.

432
00:30:04,790 --> 00:30:06,750
By the way, I wonder

433
00:30:06,750 --> 00:30:09,270
who is this generous buyer?

434
00:30:09,270 --> 00:30:11,310
How would I know? The platform protects

435
00:30:11,310 --> 00:30:13,647
the privacy of buyers. I can't look it up.

436
00:30:13,647 --> 00:30:16,680
Don't worry. My clothes are in good condition
and I priced it super low,

437
00:30:16,680 --> 00:30:17,920
the buyer won't lose out.

438
00:30:17,920 --> 00:30:19,530
I got rid of the idle clothes,

439
00:30:19,530 --> 00:30:21,510
and you'll sleep well.

440
00:30:21,510 --> 00:30:23,489
It's a win-win-win.

441
00:30:24,310 --> 00:30:25,957
All right.

442
00:30:25,957 --> 00:30:28,804
[Message me if interested.
Price: 1299 yuan. Seller: Sunny Qing]

443
00:30:28,804 --> 00:30:30,691
[Delivery status: Delivered.]

444
00:30:44,030 --> 00:30:46,591
This mattress is quite big.

445
00:30:48,550 --> 00:30:51,640
You didn't go on the trip with Shu Han.

446
00:30:51,640 --> 00:30:53,809
Do you regret it?

447
00:30:56,200 --> 00:30:57,840
No.

448
00:31:00,960 --> 00:31:02,070
That's right.

449
00:31:02,070 --> 00:31:04,435
You didn't want to go, after all.

450
00:31:07,070 --> 00:31:08,960
What about you?

451
00:31:08,960 --> 00:31:10,840
Do you regret staying here?

452
00:31:10,840 --> 00:31:12,708
I do.

453
00:31:17,470 --> 00:31:20,059
Only for a second.

454
00:31:25,310 --> 00:31:27,640
Why don't you go with Meng Rui Hang?

455
00:31:27,640 --> 00:31:30,580
Because that's not what I want.

456
00:31:35,200 --> 00:31:36,920
Lie down and see how it feels.

457
00:31:36,920 --> 00:31:39,200
It's big and soft.

458
00:31:39,200 --> 00:31:42,592
Like a cloud. Get a feel for it.

459
00:31:51,640 --> 00:31:53,524
How is it?

460
00:31:54,750 --> 00:31:58,030
I've never laid down like this in a car before.

461
00:31:58,030 --> 00:32:00,370
[Lalamove]
It's quite comfortable.

462
00:32:01,640 --> 00:32:03,470
Actually,

463
00:32:03,470 --> 00:32:07,230
the days I spend in Zhazhating

464
00:32:07,230 --> 00:32:10,310
are days I didn't dare to imagine it before.

465
00:32:10,310 --> 00:32:12,710
I've gone through so much exciting

466
00:32:12,710 --> 00:32:14,820
and unforgettable experience.

467
00:32:18,400 --> 00:32:20,320
So I'm reluctant

468
00:32:20,320 --> 00:32:22,597
to leave.

469
00:32:27,640 --> 00:32:29,521
Qing Ye,

470
00:32:31,470 --> 00:32:33,790
stay here,

471
00:32:33,790 --> 00:32:36,048
and I won't let you regret it.

472
00:32:38,790 --> 00:32:40,900
What did you say?

473
00:32:51,510 --> 00:32:53,440
I said,

474
00:32:55,400 --> 00:32:57,939
if you linger here too long,

475
00:32:58,750 --> 00:33:00,916
you'll surely regret it.

476
00:34:13,400 --> 00:34:15,150
They're on the way home, right?

477
00:34:15,150 --> 00:34:16,190
Yes.

478
00:34:16,190 --> 00:34:20,024
Wu just called me.
He said they're on their way.

479
00:34:32,200 --> 00:34:33,670
- Grandma.
- Wu.

480
00:34:33,670 --> 00:34:35,462
Where's Ye?

481
00:34:36,280 --> 00:34:37,843
Grandma.

482
00:34:38,550 --> 00:34:39,990
- You are here.
- Auntie.

483
00:34:39,990 --> 00:34:41,440
Give me a hug.

484
00:34:41,440 --> 00:34:43,570
Why are you at the door?

485
00:34:43,570 --> 00:34:45,990
We're waiting for you.

486
00:34:45,990 --> 00:34:49,190
Yes. Wu told me on the phone.
He said you were still here.

487
00:34:49,190 --> 00:34:52,110
So we might as well wait for you at the door.

488
00:34:52,110 --> 00:34:54,129
We can eat together when you get back.

489
00:34:54,129 --> 00:34:55,320
I told you.

490
00:34:55,320 --> 00:34:58,440
She never thought of leaving.

491
00:34:58,440 --> 00:35:01,080
You know me.

492
00:35:01,080 --> 00:35:03,200
The point is, you scared me.

493
00:35:03,200 --> 00:35:06,470
You even took the Welwitschia away,
so I thought you really left.

494
00:35:06,470 --> 00:35:09,320
- No, she didn't. The Welwitschia is in my room.
- Really?

495
00:35:09,320 --> 00:35:12,550
I didn't know what the Welwitschia is
so Ye showed it to me.

496
00:35:12,550 --> 00:35:14,320
Here's the thing.

497
00:35:14,320 --> 00:35:17,360
If I were leaving, I would let you know.

498
00:35:17,360 --> 00:35:18,400
Besides,

499
00:35:18,400 --> 00:35:20,477
I'm not leaving either.

500
00:35:23,630 --> 00:35:26,150
All right.

501
00:35:26,150 --> 00:35:27,880
Wait. Why did you come back in this car?

502
00:35:27,880 --> 00:35:29,920
- The stuff we bought is still in the car.
- Yes.

503
00:35:29,920 --> 00:35:31,670
- Liu Nian.
- Coming!

504
00:35:31,670 --> 00:35:32,800
Come and help.

505
00:35:32,800 --> 00:35:34,280
- Take it easy.
- Okay.

506
00:35:34,280 --> 00:35:36,630
- Here, take the back.
- Okay.

507
00:35:36,630 --> 00:35:38,990
You bought a mattress?

508
00:35:38,990 --> 00:35:40,550
Qing Ye bought it for me.

509
00:35:40,550 --> 00:35:42,139
She insisted on buying it.

510
00:35:42,920 --> 00:35:45,116
Mom, have a talk with her.

511
00:35:46,880 --> 00:35:48,190
Oh.

512
00:35:48,190 --> 00:35:49,320
All my doing.

513
00:35:49,320 --> 00:35:52,032
I spend money like water. Give me a lesson.

514
00:35:54,320 --> 00:35:56,280
Good job.

515
00:35:57,920 --> 00:36:01,440
This is from Xi Xi. She pickled it recently.

516
00:36:01,440 --> 00:36:03,840
And this, Uncle Pocky's pasture-raised chicken.

517
00:36:03,840 --> 00:36:05,840
I cooked these two dishes.

518
00:36:05,840 --> 00:36:07,470
Let's dig in.

519
00:36:07,470 --> 00:36:09,550
- I'll try yours first.
- I'm going to try yours, too.

520
00:36:09,550 --> 00:36:12,590
- I think my cooking is pretty good, too.
- Okay.

521
00:36:12,590 --> 00:36:13,960
Ye, have some chicken.

522
00:36:13,960 --> 00:36:16,071
- Tastes good, huh?
- Good!

523
00:36:16,720 --> 00:36:17,752
Well, today,

524
00:36:17,752 --> 00:36:20,280
Liu Nian and I
have been busy from morning to night.

525
00:36:20,280 --> 00:36:22,760
Our debt will be paid off soon.

526
00:36:22,760 --> 00:36:24,571
- Really? That's great.
- Really.

527
00:36:24,571 --> 00:36:25,590
Trust me.

528
00:36:25,590 --> 00:36:26,760
I trust you.

529
00:36:26,760 --> 00:36:29,123
I trust everyone.

530
00:36:38,360 --> 00:36:40,720
It's the wardrobe!

531
00:36:40,720 --> 00:36:43,030
So you were making it for me.

532
00:36:43,030 --> 00:36:44,960
Yes, but it's a pity that

533
00:36:44,960 --> 00:36:47,070
your clothes are sold
on the secondhand trading website.

534
00:36:47,070 --> 00:36:48,630
There aren't many left.

535
00:36:48,630 --> 00:36:49,920
Nothing to be sorry about.

536
00:36:49,920 --> 00:36:51,880
It can hold books instead.

537
00:36:51,880 --> 00:36:52,880
Sure.

538
00:36:52,880 --> 00:36:54,320
Put in whatever you want.

539
00:36:54,320 --> 00:36:56,240
It's done anyway.

540
00:36:56,240 --> 00:36:57,920
The new semester is about to start.

541
00:36:57,920 --> 00:37:00,480
I'll work hard to be

542
00:37:00,480 --> 00:37:02,920
the top scorer in Zhazhating.

543
00:37:02,920 --> 00:37:04,240
You will make it.

544
00:37:04,240 --> 00:37:06,070
Of course.

545
00:37:50,670 --> 00:37:52,315
<i>Qing Ye,</i>

546
00:37:53,030 --> 00:37:55,320
<i>stay here,</i>

547
00:37:55,320 --> 00:37:57,654
<i>and I won't let you regret it.</i>

548
00:38:58,320 --> 00:39:00,550
How is it? Are you having fun?

549
00:39:00,550 --> 00:39:01,760
Of course.

550
00:39:01,760 --> 00:39:03,440
I haven't been to an amusement park
for a long time.

551
00:39:03,440 --> 00:39:06,440
- Good to unwind before the term begins.
- Good.

552
00:39:06,440 --> 00:39:08,222
Let's go.

553
00:39:46,320 --> 00:39:48,081
It tastes good.

554
00:39:53,150 --> 00:39:55,110
- Why are you smiling?
- Hold on.

555
00:39:55,110 --> 00:39:57,192
I'll take a photo of you.

556
00:39:58,440 --> 00:39:59,902
Look.

557
00:40:00,550 --> 00:40:02,832
You're so annoying.

558
00:40:26,800 --> 00:40:28,655
Xing Wu.

559
00:40:30,800 --> 00:40:32,470
- Look.
- What is it?

560
00:40:32,470 --> 00:40:35,307
A teacher from Anzi No.1 High School
just texted me.

561
00:40:35,307 --> 00:40:37,120
My enrollment is done.

562
00:40:37,120 --> 00:40:38,990
They want me to register at school next week.

563
00:40:38,990 --> 00:40:40,240
Good.

564
00:40:40,240 --> 00:40:42,840
Are you familiar with the school?

565
00:40:42,840 --> 00:40:44,642
Guess.

566
00:40:46,070 --> 00:40:47,880
I know it very well.

567
00:40:47,880 --> 00:40:50,418
Let me ride you there next week.

568
00:41:08,440 --> 00:41:10,625
I've prepared everything.

569
00:41:12,990 --> 00:41:16,110
All the documents are here.

570
00:41:16,110 --> 00:41:17,960
Uncle Sun mailed them to me last week.

571
00:41:17,960 --> 00:41:19,470
I registered today,

572
00:41:19,470 --> 00:41:20,990
school starts next week,

573
00:41:20,990 --> 00:41:24,259
and I take classes as usual.

574
00:41:27,320 --> 00:41:28,893
Qing Ye,

575
00:41:29,920 --> 00:41:31,760
to be honest,

576
00:41:31,760 --> 00:41:33,510
won't you regret staying

577
00:41:33,510 --> 00:41:34,800
in a small-town school?

578
00:41:34,800 --> 00:41:36,673
No.

579
00:41:39,160 --> 00:41:41,110
This is the best choice

580
00:41:41,110 --> 00:41:43,260
I can make right now.

581
00:41:43,880 --> 00:41:45,510
Even if it's not the best choice,

582
00:41:45,510 --> 00:41:48,240
I'll make it the best one.

583
00:41:51,110 --> 00:41:52,600
You

584
00:41:52,600 --> 00:41:54,800
don't believe me?

585
00:41:54,800 --> 00:41:56,721
I believe you.

586
00:41:57,510 --> 00:41:58,520
Let's

587
00:41:58,520 --> 00:42:00,520
go to school.

588
00:42:05,320 --> 00:42:07,320
[Anzi County No.1 Middle School]

589
00:42:19,320 --> 00:42:21,240
I'll park the bike right here.

590
00:42:21,240 --> 00:42:22,990
You're quite popular.

591
00:42:22,990 --> 00:42:25,030
The security guard didn't stop you.

592
00:42:25,030 --> 00:42:26,630
I fixed his phone a few times

593
00:42:26,630 --> 00:42:27,880
for free.

594
00:42:27,880 --> 00:42:30,590
For free? You do love helping people.

595
00:42:30,590 --> 00:42:33,280
Last time, you covered the bill
for the printer shop owner.

596
00:42:33,280 --> 00:42:35,590
It depends on my mood.

597
00:42:35,590 --> 00:42:36,880
It's a kind of social investment.

598
00:42:36,880 --> 00:42:39,339
Now I can just show my face and walk in.

599
00:42:40,150 --> 00:42:42,760
It's this building.
Go up to the third floor and then turn right.

600
00:42:42,760 --> 00:42:44,720
I'll see you off here.

601
00:42:44,720 --> 00:42:46,339
Why?

602
00:42:47,190 --> 00:42:48,840
Though the security guard didn't stop me,

603
00:42:48,840 --> 00:42:51,440
the teachers at school
won't welcome me that much.

604
00:42:51,440 --> 00:42:53,360
I'll wait for you here.

605
00:42:53,360 --> 00:42:55,619
Okay, I'll get going then.

606
00:43:10,320 --> 00:43:11,945
Come in.

607
00:43:13,590 --> 00:43:14,880
Hello.

608
00:43:14,880 --> 00:43:17,440
Here's my document.

609
00:43:17,440 --> 00:43:18,920
Qing Ye, right?

610
00:43:18,920 --> 00:43:20,640
Come, have a seat.

611
00:43:20,640 --> 00:43:22,808
I've been waiting for you.

612
00:43:26,360 --> 00:43:28,440
This is your new uniform.

613
00:43:28,440 --> 00:43:29,584
Thank you, miss.

614
00:43:29,584 --> 00:43:32,590
Our school requires students to wear uniforms.
This one is new.

615
00:43:32,590 --> 00:43:35,316
- Please sign here.
- Sure.

616
00:43:40,400 --> 00:43:42,545
Got a minute?
